{"parse":{"title":"Protected enclosure (or machine)","pageid":2100,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>6-8-235</b>\n</p><p>An enclosure (or machine) designed to restrict or prevent the ingress of liquids or solid particles in harmful quantities, or solid extraneous objects of specified size.\n</p><p><br>\nNote: 1   See also 6-4-140.\n</p><p><br>\nNote: 2  The different categories of protection are specified for enclosures in <span class=\"mw-lingo-term\" data-lingo-term-id=\"c221291e3a0d7879b5dabb8a6b10903f\">IEC</span> 529, and for machines in <span class=\"mw-lingo-term\" data-lingo-term-id=\"c221291e3a0d7879b5dabb8a6b10903f\">IEC</span> 34-5.\n</p><p><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<i>Please note that this is the term as it stands in the original <span class=\"mw-lingo-term\" data-lingo-term-id=\"0a1217bfe27a54fc7e55b72fc62c2371\">IALA</span> Dictionary edition (1970-1989)</i>\n<br>\n</p>\n<div class=\"LanguageLinks\">\n<table width=\"100%\">\n<tbody><tr valign=\"top\" style=\"background: #FFFFFF\">\n<td style=\"width: 25px; padding-left: 0em; border-right: 1px solid #aaaaaa;border-left: 1px solid #EEF3E2;border-top: 1px solid #EEF3E2;border-bottom: 1px solid #EEF3E2;\"><span typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"/wiki/dictionary/index.php/File:25px-Geographylogo.png\" class=\"mw-file-description\" title=\"Languages\"><img alt=\"Languages\" src=\"/wiki/dictionary/images/8/82/25px-Geographylogo.png\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"25\" height=\"25\" class=\"mw-file-element\"></a></span></td>\n<td style=\"padding: 1px 1em 0; background: #EEF3E2;\">\n<p><b><a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">English</a></b>\n<span></span>\n<span></span>\n<span></span>\n<span></span>\n</p>\n</td></tr></tbody></table></div></div><div class=\"mw-lingo-tooltip\" id=\"c221291e3a0d7879b5dabb8a6b10903f\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition navigation-not-searchable\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition-text\">\n<p>International Electrotechnical Commission\n</p>\n</div></div>\n<